habitat_description: The Georgetown salamander has been recently described from springs of the San Gabriel River drainage near Georgetown in Williamson County, Texas at an elevation of 230 meters (Chippindale et al. 2000; Lannoo 2005; Green et al. 2013). This species is completely aquatic and individuals are usually found in spring outflows, under gravel substrate, under rocks, under leaves, and in caves.
